## Step 6: Execution order

1. Create Alembic migration: add `categories_key`, populate from existing `category_id`
2. Modify `backend/app/models.py` — add `categories_key` columns
3. Modify `backend/app/similarity.py` — add combination computation helpers
4. Modify `backend/app/embedding.py` — support `categories_key` in `compute_group_group_matrix`
5. Modify `backend/app/schemas.py` — add `categories_key` to response models
6. Modify `backend/app/api/routes.py` — accept `categories` list param, build composite key
7. Modify `backend/scripts/compute_similarities.py` — enumerate & precompute combinations
8. Re-run `python -m backend.scripts.compute_similarities` to populate all data
9. Modify `frontend/src/stores/ui-store.ts` — replace `selectedCategory` with `selectedCategories`
10. Modify `frontend/src/api/{embeddings,voters,groups}.ts` — pass categories array
11. Modify `frontend/src/stores/{embeddings,voters,groups}-store.ts` — update method signatures
12. Rewrite `frontend/src/components/shared/category-filter.tsx` — multi-select Autocomplete
13. Update `frontend/src/pages/{map,voter-detail,group-detail}-page.tsx` — wire new store API
14. Update `frontend/src/constants/fr.ts` — label text
15. Update `frontend/src/api/types.ts` — add `categories_key` to response types
16. Verify with test data: seed + compute → run frontend → test single/multi/global filters
